18/11/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The biannual meetings of the Stability Pact for Southeast Europe began in Skopje Wednesday (17 November), including regional tables on Democratisation and Human Rights, Economic Reconstruction, Development and Co-operation, and Security.
Attending the three-day forum are representatives of regional governments, the EU and the United States, UNMIK, the OSCE, the Council of Europe and international financial institutions.
During the opening of the security table's session, the countries were urged to co-operate closely to fight organised crime and to bring their respective laws into line with EU and international standards.
(Dnevnik - 18/11/04)
